Study: Characteristics and Outcomes of COVID-19 Patients in New York City's Public Hospital System
Study Population: New York City Health and Hospital between March 5 and April 9, 2020

Study: Factors associated with hospital admission and critical illness among 5279 people with coronavirus disease 2019 in New York City: prospective cohort study
Study Population: NYU Langone Health between March 1, 2020 to April 8, 2020

Study: Type 1 and Type 2 diabetes and COVID-19 related mortality in England: a whole population study
Multivariate adjustment: age, sex, deprivation, ethnicity, region, heart disease, cerebrovascular disease, heart failure, diabetes
Study Population: All individuals registered with a GP practice in England and alive on the 19th February; data extracted on May 11, 2020.

Study: Factors Associated With Intubation and Prolonged Intubation in Hospitalized Patients With COVID-19
Multivariate adjustment: Age; Sex; Race and Ethnicity; Hospital; BMI; Respiratory rate; Temperature; Oxygen Saturation; Pulse; Diabetes; Shortness of breath
Study Population: Ten hospitals in the Chicago metropolitan area from March 1, 2020 to April 8, 2020

Study: Risk factors for clinical progression in patients with COVID-19: a retrospective study of electronic health record data in the United Kingdom
Multivariate adjustment: Age; Ethnicity; Laboratory values; Vital signs
Study Population: Emergency department of Chelsea & Westminster Hospital NHS Foundation Trust between 1st January 2020 and 23rd April 2020

Study: OpenSAFELY: factors associated with COVID-19-related hospital death in the linked electronic health records of 17 million adult NHS patients.
Multivariate adjustment: age, gender, obesity, smoking status, diabetes, cancer, hematological malignancy, asthma, chronic respiratory disease, heart disease, hypertension, chronic liver disease, stroke or dementia, other neurological disease, reduced kidney function, organ transplant, spleen disease, rheumatoid arthritis/lupus/psoriasis, immunosuppression
Study Population: TPP general practice in England from February 1 to April 25, 2020.

Study: Estimating Survival of Hospitalized COVID-19 Patients from Admission Information
Study Population: Northwell Health acute care hospitals on or after March 1, 2020, and were discharged or died before April 12, 2020. Clinical outcomes (i.e., discharges, mortality, and length of stay) were monitored until April 12, 2020, the final date of follow-up

Study: Clinical Characteristics of Hospitalized Covid-19 Patients in New York City
Study Population: Mount Sinai Hospital located in East Harlem, Manhattan; Mount Sinai Morningside located in Morningside Heights, Manhattan; Mount Sinai West located in Midtown and the West Side, Manhattan; Mount Sinai Brooklyn located in Midwood, Brooklyn; and Mount Sinai Queens located in Astoria, Queens from Feb 27, 2020 to Apr 2, 2020
